#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch032_networking-best-practices.xml:78(para)
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Overlapping IP addresses</emphasis>Linux network "
"namespaces are required on nodes running neutron-l3-agent or neutron-dhcp-"
"agent if overlapping IP's are in use. In order to support overlapping IP "
"addresses, the OpenStack Networking DHCP and L3 agents use Linux network "
"namespaces by default. If the host does not support namespaces then the "
"<literal>neutron-l3-agent</literal> and <literal>neutron-dhcp-agent</"
"literal> should be run on different hosts."
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch032_networking-best-practices.xml:79(para)
msgid ""
"A further limitation of the L3 Agent is the support a single logical router "
"without namespaces."
